================================================================
gCTLN w/ SOFTPLUS SMOOTHING — 3-sine-wave toy problem
================================================================

Architecture:
  GCTLNPerEdge with per-edge weight learning
  ODE: dx/dt = -x + softplus(W·x + θ, β)
       (softplus replaces torch.clamp to smooth gradients
        through the adjoint method)

Task: fit three non-negative sines at 120° phase offsets
      x_i(t) = 0.4·sin(t + i·2π/3) + 0.5   on a 3-cycle motif

Purpose: test whether smoothed CTLN dynamics enable
         gradient-based discovery of oscillatory regimes
         (previously failed under piecewise-linear ReLU).
================================================================

Configuration:
  Script:   scripts/gctln_w_uniq_edges.py
  Output:   /scratch/xfd3tf/gctln_smooth
  Device:   CPU (3-neuron CTLN, 1k timesteps)
  Threads:  1
================================================================

